A GAS leak has sparked a major evacuation of a Scots college while nearby resident have been warned to remain indoors.
More than 1300 people were forced to leave South Lanarkshire College in East Kilbride after the alarm was raised at 9.30am this morning.
Firefighters are working with specialist services - including gas distribution firm SGN - to make the college safe.
The college has been sealed off with a cordon and several roads have been closed in the immediate area.
The A725 Strathaven Road, Burniehill Roundabout and Torrance Roundabout are all currently closed.
